The paper discusses alternative architectures and computational models for faster and more energy-efficient application-level tasks, which suggests a focus on embedded systems and hardware acceleration. The use of cellular neural networks (CeNNs) also points towards the areas of neural networks and analog circuits (cs.NE and cs.AR). The case study on target-tracking suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), while the evaluation framework and comparison to von Neumann algorithms suggest a focus on system-level design and optimization (cs.SY). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
